Package: proRate
Title: Infer RNA Polymerase II elongation rate from Pro-seq
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Yu",
           family = "Liu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "yuabrahamliu@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8631-4347")), 
    person(given = "Fadhl", 
	       family = "Alakwaa", 
		   role = c("aut"), 
		   email = "alakwaaf@med.umich.edu", 
		   comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5349-7960")))
Description: The main purpose of this R package is to provide functions used 
    to infer RNA Polymerase II (PolII) elongation rate from Pro-seq/Gro-seq 
	data using a novel least sum of square (LSS) method. It also contains 
	other functions to do metagene plotting, pausing index calculation, and 
	gene structure analysis, etc.
